Scan Apps with MobSF and Analyze Findings
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure Mobile Security Framework (MobSF) for Android APK analysis
Upload and scan Android applications using MobSF web interface and API
Interpret security vulnerability findings from MobSF scan reports
Automate batch scanning of multiple APK files using Python scripts
Generate comprehensive security assessment reports based on scan results
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of Android application architecture and APK structure
Familiarity with Python programming fundamentals
Knowledge of common mobile security vulnerabilities (OWASP Mobile Top 10)
