Task 1: Install and Configure MobSF
Step 1.1: Install System Dependencies
Update your system and install required packages:

# Update system packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Python 3, pip, and dependencies
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv git wget openjdk-8-jdk -y

# Verify Java installation
java -version
Step 1.2: Download and Setup MobSF
Clone the MobSF repository and install dependencies:

# Create directory and clone MobSF
mkdir ~/security-tools && cd ~/security-tools
git clone https://github.com/MobSF/Mobile-Security-Framework-MobSF.git
cd Mobile-Security-Framework-MobSF

# Create and activate virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
./setup.sh
Step 1.3: Start MobSF Server
Launch the MobSF web interface:

# Start MobSF server (keep terminal open)
python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000

# In a new terminal, verify MobSF is running
curl -I http://localhost:8000
Expected Output: HTTP/1.1 200 OK

Step 1.4: Download Sample APK Files
Prepare vulnerable Android applications for testing:

# Create APK samples directory
mkdir ~/apk-samples && cd ~/apk-samples

# Download DIVA (Damn Insecure and Vulnerable App)
wget https://github.com/payatu/diva-android/releases/download/v1.0/diva-beta.apk

# Download InsecureBankv2
wget https://github.com/dineshshetty/Android-InsecureBankv2/releases/download/v1.0/InsecureBankv2.apk

# Verify downloads
ls -lh *.apk
