Step 3.2: Review Key Security Findings
When analyzing MobSF results, focus on:

Critical Areas:

Security Score: Overall security rating (0-100)
High Severity Issues: Immediate security risks requiring attention
Dangerous Permissions: Permissions that access sensitive data/features
Code Analysis: Hardcoded secrets, insecure cryptography, SQL injection
Certificate Analysis: Signing certificate validity and strength
Network Security: Cleartext traffic, SSL/TLS configuration
Common Vulnerabilities in DIVA:

Insecure data storage (SharedPreferences, SQLite)
Hardcoded credentials and API keys
Insecure communication (HTTP instead of HTTPS)
Weak cryptographic implementations
Input validation issues
Insecure Android component exports
